{
  "texts": [
    "Biblioshiny was employed for the overview analysis of the retrieved documents, relevant keyword analysis, and plotting the three-field Sankey Diagrams.",
    "VOSviewer software was used to illustrate various collaboration networks, perform citation and co-citation analysis, and identify the top five keywords along with their co-occurrence networks.",
    "Various indicators have been used in the literature for bibliometric analysis, including total article count, average citations per article (ACPA), total citation count, total link strength, and Hirsch index (Hindex).",
    "These metrics are commonly used in bibliometric studies, with the H-index being a widely recognized measure of research quality and quantity for authors and research areas (Farhat et al., 2023a).",
    "ACPA is also widely accepted as a measure of research impact for individual works, authors, and publication outlets."
  ]
}